onButtons` uses `SwActionButton(onTap: ...)`. The SwActionButton internally uses
`onTapDown`, so that's fine.\n   - But wait, `GestureDetector` on the card stack
in `home_page.dart` uses `onHorizontalDragUpdate` and `onHorizontalDragEnd` - th
ose should be fine since they're for gestures, not Maestro taps.\n\n3. Let me ch
eck if there are any issues with the `ProfileCompletionGuard` - does it exist?\n
\n4. Check the `matching_socket_client.dart` - it uses `String.fromEnvironment('
API_BASE_URL')` but the DioClient uses a different base URL mechanism. This coul
d be inconsistent.\n\n5. Check the BDD tests for completeness.\n\n6. Check if th
ere are issues with the design system components not using `Positioned` in Stack
. Looking at `swipe_card_stack.dart`, it uses `Positioned` for the third card, b
ut the second card uses `_buildBackgroundCard(cards[1])` without `Positioned`. I
s this in a Stack? Yes. The second card will be positioned by default at top-lef
t. But the `SwipeCard` has margin, so it might be okay. However, for the `SwipeC
ardStack`, cards 2+ are not using Positioned, they rely on Stack's default align
ment (`Alignment.center`). That's actually fine since Stack default alignment is
center.\n\nWait, looking more carefully at `swipe_card_stack.dart`:\n```dart\nre
turn Stack(\n  alignment: Alignment.center,\n  children: [\n    if (cards.length
> 1) _buildBackgroundCard(cards[1]),\n    if (cards.length > 2)\n      Positione
d(\n        top: 8,\n        left: 0,\n        right: 0,\n        child: _buildB
ackgroundCard(cards[2], scale: 0.9),\n      ),\n    SwipeCard(...),\n  ],\n);\n`
``\n\nThe second card (cards[1]) is not wrapped in Positioned but Stack alignmen
t is center, so it's fine. The third card uses Positioned(top: 8, left: 0, right
: 0) but this doesn't have height specified. Could this cause accessibility boun
ds issues? Since it has `left: 0, right: 0`, the width is constrained. The child
is a Transform.scale -> Opacity -> SwipeCard, and SwipeCard has margin and Aspec
tRatio, so height is determined by the child. This should be okay.\n\n7. Looking
at `swipe_card.dart`, the `Stack` inside the card has `Positioned(bottom: 0, lef
t: 0, right: 0)` for the gradient overlay - this is fine because it has left/rig
ht constraints.\n\n8. Let me check if there are any hardcoded colors in the new 
