    type='think',
    think='Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me check a few more thi
ngs:\n\n1. The `designs/issue-43/` directory exists, which means the design-only
PR process might have been followed. But the current PR is `feat/issue-43` and i
ncludes direct changes to `packages/design-system/` and `apps/mobile/`. Accordin
g to `flutter.md`, "禁止在 Design-Only PR 中直接写入 packages/、apps/ 或仓库根目
录下的任何正式代码文件". But this is a `feat` PR, not a `design` PR. The questio
n is whether a Design-Only PR was merged before this one. The existence of `desi
gns/issue-43/` suggests it might have been done. However, the current PR include
s design system changes directly in `packages/design-system/`. Since this is a `
feat` PR, it\'s supposed to write code directly. The design-only PR requirement 
is for when you need to add new UI components. If a design-only PR was already d
one, then this feat PR can migrate the widgets into packages/. So this is likely
fine.\n\n2. Let me check if there are any issues with the `MatchingSocketClient`
in `home_page.dart`. The `_initSocket` method reads the access token from `Secur
eStorage()` directly, rather than using the auth bloc\'s token or a repository. 
This is inconsistent but functional.\n\n3. Another critical thing: in `home_page
.dart`, `_initSocket` is called in `initState`. But `initState` runs before the 
widget is fully mounted, and `context.read<AuthBloc>()` works in `initState`. Ho
wever, if the auth state changes later (e.g., token refresh), the socket won\'t 
be re-initialized with the new token. This is a minor issue.\n\n4. Looking at `m
atching_socket_client.dart`, it uses `io.io(serverUrl, ...)` with `autoConnect: 
true`. But then `connect()` is called explicitly. With `autoConnect: true`, the 
socket connects immediately upon creation. Calling `connect()` again is redundan
t but harmless.\n\n5. Let me check if there are any issues with the `matching.se
rvice.ts` `getMatchList` method. It queries matches with `innerJoinAndSelect("m.
user_a", "ua")` and `innerJoinAndSelect("m.user_b", "ub")`. But `MatchEntity` do
esn\'t have relations defined for `user_a` and `user_b`. Looking at the entity:\
n```typescript\n@Entity("matches")\nexport class MatchEntity {\n  @PrimaryColumn
("char", { length: 36 })\n  id: string;\n\n  @Column("char", { length: 36 })\n  
user_a_id: string;\n\n  @Column("char", { length: 36 })\n  user_b_id: string;\n 
...\n}\n```\nThere are no `@ManyToOne` relations to UserEntity. So `innerJoinAnd
Select("m.user_a", "ua")` will fail at runtime because TypeORM can\'t find the r
elation "user_a". This is a **Blocking** bug!\n\nWait, let me verify. In `getMat
chList`:\n```typescript\nconst qb = this.matchRepo\n  .createQueryBuilder("m")\n
 .innerJoinAndSelect("m.user_a", "ua")\n  .innerJoinAndSelect("m.user_b", "ub")\
n```\n\nIf `MatchEntity` doesn\'t have relations `user_a` and `user_b`, this que
ry will throw an error. Let me check the entity again from main.\n\nYes, from ma
in:\n```typescript\n@Entity("matches")\nexport class MatchEntity {\n  @PrimaryCo
lumn("char", { length: 36 })\n  id: string;\n\n  @Column("char", { length: 36 })
\n  user_a_id: string;\n\n  @Column("char", { length: 36 })\n  user_b_id: string
;\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nNo relations! So `innerJoinAndSelect("m.user_a", "ua")` will
definitely fail. The service then never uses `ua` or `ub` in the result - it onl
y uses `m.user_a_id` and `m.user_b_id`. So these joins are unnecessary and will 
cause runtime errors. This is a Blocking issue.\n\n6. Let me also check if there
are similar issues in other parts of matching.service.ts. The `checkAndCreateMut
ualMatch` method uses `manager.create(MatchEntity, ...)` and `manager.save(Match
Entity, ...)` which is fine. It doesn\'t use relations.\n\n7. Another potential 
issue: `matching.service.ts` `queryCandidatesFromDb` SQL query uses `u.id NOT IN
(... UNION ...)` with 6 subqueries. If any of these subqueries returns NULL, the
`NOT IN` will fail. But looking at the subqueries, they all select from tables w
ith non-nullable ID columns, so this is fine.\n\n8. Another issue: in `matching.
service.ts` `queryCandidatesFromDb`, the SQL uses `u.last_login_at` but the scor
ing uses `last_login_at` for activity. The PRD says "近期活跃用户优先（权重 30%
）：根据 last_active_at 分档". But the entity uses `last_login_at`. This is an e
xisting schema discrepancy, not introduced by this PR.\n\n9. Check `matching.ser
vice.ts` `getRecommendations` for cache hit path: it parses cached data and call
s `buildRecommendations`. But `buildRecommendations` fetches profiles by IDs. If
a user has updated their profile (e.g., changed avatar) since the cache was buil
t, the cache hit will return stale data. The cache TTL is 5 minutes, which is ac
ceptable per PRD.\n\n10. Check `matching.service.ts` `recordSwipeAction`: it cle
ars cache for both actor and target. But for the target, it clears all three mod
e caches. However, if the target currently has a cached recommendation list that
includes the actor, that cache is now stale because the actor liked the target. 
But since the target won\'t see the actor anymore (the actor is excluded by `mat
ch_actions` check), clearing the cache is actually not strictly necessary for co
rrectness. But it\'s good practice.\n\n11. Check `matching.service.ts` `getMatch
