ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='So the `matching/` directory didn\'t exist in origin/main at all. It 
was created in this PR. And the PR creates matching flows that reference `includ
es/login-as-test-user.yaml` but doesn\'t create a symlink `includes -> ../../inc
ludes` in the `matching/` directory. This means the Maestro flows will fail beca
use they can\'t find the include file.\n\nThis is a **Blocking** issue.\n\nNow l
et me compile all my findings:\n\n**Blocking Issues:**\n1. `matching.service.ts`
`getMatchList` uses `innerJoinAndSelect("m.user_a", "ua")` and `innerJoinAndSele
ct("m.user_b", "ub")` but `MatchEntity` has no `user_a`/`user_b` relations defin
ed. Runtime TypeORM error.\n2. `.maestro/flows/matching/` missing `includes` sym
link to `../../includes`, causing `runFlow: includes/login-as-test-user.yaml` to
fail.\n\n**Major Issues:**\n3. `matching_socket_client.dart` uses `String.fromEn
vironment(\'API_BASE_URL\')` instead of sharing DioClient\'s base URL configurat
ion. Runtime URL changes (e.g., via DevTools) won\'t affect Socket.io connection
s.\n4. `matching.controller.ts` `/matches` endpoint allows `limit` up to 100, bu
t API contract specifies max 50.\n5. `matching.service.ts` `getRecommendations` 
DB path can return `avatar_url: null` which violates `RecommendationResponseDto`
interface (`avatar_url: string`).\n6. `matching.service.ts` cache lock fallback 
doesn\'t prevent cache stampede (falls through to DB without lock if retry cache
miss).\n7. `matching.gateway.ts` uses `process.env.CLIENT_URL` directly instead 
of config module.\n8. `matching.module.ts` imports `BlockEntity` from another mo
dule (`../blocks/block.entity`), violating module decoupling principle.\n\n**Min
or Issues:**\n9. Some hardcoded colors in design system components (`Colors.whit
e70`, `Colors.black.withOpacity(0.8)` in swipe_card.dart and match_success_dialo
g.dart) - but these are overlay/semantic colors without tokens.\n10. `matching_s
ocket_client.dart` uses `autoConnect: true` and then calls `connect()` redundant
ly.\n11. `home_page.dart` doesn\'t re-initialize socket on token refresh.\n12. `
swipe_card_stack.dart` background cards don\'t have `Positioned` but rely on Sta
ck alignment - this is actually fine.\n13. Golden files were updated for login p
age etc. - these are minor pixel differences.\n\nWait, let me re-evaluate some o
f these:\n\nIssue 1 is definitely Blocking. The code will crash when `getMatchLi
st` is called.\n\nIssue 2 is Blocking for E2E tests.\n\nIssue 3: The socket clie
nt uses compile-time env vars while DioClient probably uses runtime config. This
is an architectural inconsistency but won\'t break the app in production if `API
_BASE_URL` is properly set at build time. However, it breaks the dev tools hot-u
pdate functionality. I\'d rate this Major.\n\nIssue 4: Limit validation inconsis
tency. The controller allows 100 but spec says 50. This is a contract violation.
Major.\n\nIssue 5: `avatar_url` can be null. The client probably handles it, but
it\'s a DTO contract violation. Major.\n\nIssue 6: Cache stampede on lock failur
e. The PRD specifically mentions "缓存击穿防护：使用互斥锁". If lock fails and c
ache is still empty, it falls through to DB without lock. This defeats the purpo
se. Major.\n\nIssue 7: Direct `process.env` access. Per NestJS standard, this is
a violation. Minor to Major.\n\nIssue 8: Cross-module entity import. The standar
d says "禁止直接 import 其他模块的内部 Service". Entities are not services, but 
it\'s still coupling. I\'d say Minor.\n\nNow let me also check one more thing: t
he `matching.service.ts` `queryCandidatesFromDb` SQL uses `u.last_login_at` but 
the PRD says `last_active_at`. However, looking at the user entity, it\'s `last_
